sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Frontend as Frontend<br/>(Next.js)
    participant API as Server API<br/>(FastAPI)
    participant Agent as Multi-Agent System<br/>(starboard-server)
    participant Core as Core Models<br/>(starboard-core)
    participant Tools as Tools<br/>(starboard-server)
    participant DB as Databricks API
    
    User->>Frontend: "Analyze job 123"
    
    Note over Frontend: Step 1: User Request
    
    Frontend->>API: POST /api/chat/messages<br/>{message, conversation_id}
    
    Note over API: Step 2: API Layer
    
    API->>API: Authenticate & validate
    API->>Agent: handle_message(message)
    
    Note over Agent: Step 3: Agent Processing
    
    Agent->>Core: Load Message model
    Core-->>Agent: Message instance
    
    Agent->>Agent: Route to JobAgent<br/>(IntentRouter)
    
    Agent->>Tools: execute_tool("resolve_job", {job_id: "123"})
    
    Note over Tools: Step 4: Tool Execution
    
    Tools->>DB: GET /api/2.0/jobs/get?job_id=123
    DB-->>Tools: Job metadata
    
    Tools->>DB: GET /api/2.0/jobs/runs/list
    DB-->>Tools: Job runs data
    
    Tools-->>Agent: ToolResult {job_data, runs, ...}
    
    Note over Agent: Step 5: Process Results
    
    Agent->>Core: Create Episode (working memory)
    Core-->>Agent: Episode instance
    
    Agent->>Agent: Generate recommendations<br/>(LLM reasoning)
    
    Agent->>Core: Create output Message
    Core-->>Agent: Message instance
    
    Agent-->>API: FinalOutputEvent
    
    Note over API: Step 6: Stream Response
    
    API->>Frontend: SSE: final_output<br/>{recommendations, metadata}
    
    Note over API: Step 7: Persist Conversation
    
    API->>Core: Conversation model
    Core-->>API: Immutable Conversation
    API->>API: Save to database
    
    Frontend->>User: Display recommendations
    
    Note over User: Main request flow complete<br/>Frontend → API → Agent → Tools → Databricks

